  "conclusion": "Under KITTI full-sequence odometry with constant-velocity prediction, fixed fine sigma keeps KC-LO accuracy within 1% RPE of the annealed profile while improving throughput by about 1.9x on seq00 and 2.2x on seq07. The kernel-correlation mechanism is the main positive signal; sigma annealing appears to be a convergence-safety knob rather than necessary for this well-initialized protocol."
